00:10:28.310 --> 00:10:30.990
The Tiger Child

00:10:30.990 --> 00:10:36.220
Jennifer Pan is the daughter of Vietnamese-
born immigrants, Bich (bik) and Hann who settled

00:10:36.220 --> 00:10:38.380
down in Toronto, Canada.

00:10:38.380 --> 00:10:43.370
Because of her parents’ Vietnamese upbringing
they had a very specific parenting style known

00:10:43.370 --> 00:10:48.380
today as “tiger parenting”, where strict
rules are enforced, expectations are high,

00:10:48.380 --> 00:10:52.570
and very little praise is given to children
no matter what their achievements.

00:10:52.570 --> 00:10:58.670
Bich and Hann Pak were hardworking and thrifty
citizens who used their earnings from an auto

00:10:58.670 --> 00:11:05.060
part factory both worked at were able to buy
themselves a large house and nice cars.

00:11:05.060 --> 00:11:09.959
They built a life that they wanted their children
to emulate and therefore set very high goals

00:11:09.959 --> 00:11:13.930
for Jennifer and her younger brother Felix.

00:11:13.930 --> 00:11:19.149
Made to learn piano at the age of four, Jennifer
was constantly being pushed by her father

00:11:19.149 --> 00:11:21.060
to learn new skills.

00:11:21.060 --> 00:11:25.430
She was an acclaimed figure skater and flute
player and her friends recall her fathers

00:11:25.430 --> 00:11:31.290
stern and watchful gaze as he monitored her
each and every practice.

00:11:31.290 --> 00:11:37.330
At her fathers insistent she never dated nor
did she attend any social gatherings and,

00:11:37.330 --> 00:11:42.800
by the age of 22, recalls a friend, “she
had never gone to a club been drunk visited

00:11:42.800 --> 00:11:46.920
a friends cottage or gone on vacation without
her family”.

00:11:46.920 --> 00:11:52.050
Despite her father‘s insistence that practice
makes perfect, Jennifer did not receive outstanding

00:11:52.050 --> 00:11:57.199
marks in high school academics and routinely
forged her straight A- report cards to cover

00:11:57.199 --> 00:12:00.589
up her actual grades of C’s and D’s.

00:12:00.589 --> 00:12:07.170
By senior year her lies were in surmountable
and, after failing a calculus class she had

00:12:07.170 --> 00:12:11.180
her early admission rescinded from Ryerson
University.

00:12:11.180 --> 00:12:16.209
Jennifer, too ashamed to admit to her parents
what had actually happened, pretended that

00:12:16.209 --> 00:12:20.779
she was given many scholarships in order to
go to the university for free.

00:12:20.779 --> 00:12:24.769
While her parents thought she was sitting
in college classes she was actually working

00:12:24.769 --> 00:12:28.819
at local cafés and is a private piano instructor.

00:12:28.819 --> 00:12:34.149
Jennifer kept up the lie so specifically that
she even purchased used textbooks and watch

00:12:34.149 --> 00:12:37.439
Videos related to her area of study.

00:12:37.439 --> 00:12:41.920
She then continued to deceive when she told
her parents that she was accepted and given

00:12:41.920 --> 00:12:47.120
free tuition at pharmacology program at the
University of Toronto.

00:12:47.120 --> 00:12:51.430
She then and got permission from them to live
near the college during the week.

00:12:51.430 --> 00:12:56.600
In all actuality though, she was staying with
a boy, Daniel Wong, her secret high-school

00:12:56.600 --> 00:12:57.720
lover.

00:12:57.720 --> 00:13:02.350
Her lies became too bold and too specific
however when she told her parents that she

00:13:02.350 --> 00:13:07.529
was working as a volunteer at the well known
and world-renowned Toronto Hospital for Sick

00:13:07.529 --> 00:13:09.069
Children.

00:13:09.069 --> 00:13:13.720
Her parents started questioning her story
and became suspicious when they noticed she

00:13:13.720 --> 00:13:18.579
did not have any sort of uniform or even a
hospital ID badge.

00:13:18.579 --> 00:13:23.189
Wanting to know the truth Jennifer’s mother
secretly followed her daughter into “work”

00:13:23.189 --> 00:13:26.200
and soon learned it was all a farce.

00:13:26.200 --> 00:13:31.110
Upon this realization, Jennifer’s father
wanted to kick her out of the house but, persuaded

00:13:31.110 --> 00:13:35.100
by Jennifer’s mother, the girl who lied
was allowed to stay.

00:13:35.100 --> 00:13:40.079
Through much turmoil and fighting Jennifer‘s
parents eventually learned that she had not

00:13:40.079 --> 00:13:42.060
even completed high school.

00:13:42.060 --> 00:13:46.319
But while they certainly weren’t understanding,
they did help and encourage her to take the

00:13:46.319 --> 00:13:53.940
necessary classes to get her high school diploma
so that she could apply to actual universities.

00:13:53.940 --> 00:13:58.779
However their forgiveness did not mean their
kindness, and Jennifer was very much a prisoner

00:13:58.779 --> 00:14:04.339
in her own home,not allowed to contact her
boyfriend under any circumstances.

00:14:04.339 --> 00:14:09.439
Resorting to secret telephone calls to Daniel
Jennifer soon became worried as Daniel was

00:14:09.439 --> 00:14:14.990
not as interested in her anymore due to her
extreme social restrictions.

00:14:14.990 --> 00:14:18.750
Jennifer soon found out that he was dating
another woman and that he was falling for

00:14:18.750 --> 00:14:20.449
that girl fast.

00:14:20.449 --> 00:14:25.829
To combat Daniels straying eye, Jennifer concocted
a story of a brutal break- in and subsequent

00:14:25.829 --> 00:14:26.829
attack.

00:14:26.829 --> 00:14:31.740
She also fabricated a story about a bullet
being mailed to her from Wong’s current

00:14:31.740 --> 00:14:32.740
girlfriend.

00:14:32.740 --> 00:14:36.880
Her fantastic stories seemed to be effective
and they all came to a head when Jennifer

00:14:36.880 --> 00:14:43.749
convinced Daniel to help her hire a professional
hitman for $10,000 to kill her parents.

00:14:43.749 --> 00:14:49.160
She told Daniel that the death of her parents
would lead her to inherit over $500,000 and

00:14:49.160 --> 00:14:52.569
that they could then move in together and
live happily ever after.

00:14:52.569 --> 00:14:58.769
On November 8, 2010 Jennifer, after successfully
putting the hit out on her parents, left the

00:14:58.769 --> 00:15:02.860
door to the family home unlocked before she
went to bed.

00:15:02.860 --> 00:15:07.430
Under the cover of darkness the three hitman
entered the large home and demanded all the

00:15:07.430 --> 00:15:09.850
money in the house from Jennifer‘s parents.

00:15:09.850 --> 00:15:14.189
They then took Jennifer’s parents to the
basement where they were each shot several

00:15:14.189 --> 00:15:15.189
times.

00:15:15.189 --> 00:15:18.970
Jennifer’s brother was luckily not living
with his parents by them.

00:15:18.970 --> 00:15:25.180
Jennifer‘s mother was killed but Jennifer‘s
father would shockingly survived the attack.

00:15:25.180 --> 00:15:31.740
The three men fled, having taken many of the
houses valuables as well as $2000 cash from

00:15:31.740 --> 00:15:33.230
Jennifer herself.

00:15:33.230 --> 00:15:37.829
During the attack Jennifer claims she was
tied up but that she was able to overcome

00:15:37.829 --> 00:15:40.629
her bondage and call 911.

00:15:40.629 --> 00:15:46.480
The investigation quickly focused on Jennifer
as a suspect as she was the only one unscathed.

00:15:46.480 --> 00:15:51.680
Detectives commented that it was an atypical
scenario in a home invasion to attempt to

00:15:51.680 --> 00:15:56.209
kill two of the occupants but leave one eyewitness
unharmed.

00:15:56.209 --> 00:16:01.020
Computer analysis of Jennifers testimony to
the police also revealed inconsistencies with

00:16:01.020 --> 00:16:05.790
her statement and once her father was able
to be interviewed by police his story varied

00:16:05.790 --> 00:16:07.819
drastically from Jennifer’s.

00:16:07.819 --> 00:16:13.339
Jennifer, Daniel, and the three hitman were
arrested and all given life sentences with

00:16:13.339 --> 00:16:17.920
possibility of parole after 25 years served.

00:16:17.920 --> 00:16:19.639
4.

00:16:19.639 --> 00:16:21.980
Fake Beard Bandit

00:16:21.980 --> 00:16:27.310
Known as the “Fake Beard Bandit” Brett
Ryan was no stranger to a life of crime.

00:16:27.310 --> 00:16:31.680
He had committed a string of bank robberies
while dressed as an elderly man in order to

00:16:31.680 --> 00:16:35.170
pay off his nearly 36,000 dollar debt.

00:16:35.170 --> 00:16:39.720
Telling the judge at sentencing that he had
suffered an extreme manic episode as a result

00:16:39.720 --> 00:16:44.339
of a depressive spell and his recent break
up with a girlfriend, the judge gave him a

00:16:44.339 --> 00:16:48.660
light sentence of only 3 years and nine months.

00:16:48.660 --> 00:16:53.939
In prison he had good behavior and was released
on “day parole” which allowed him to only

00:16:53.939 --> 00:16:56.529
come back to prison to sleep.

00:16:56.529 --> 00:17:02.319
When he got out for good, he got engaged to
Kristen Baxter, a woman he met presumably

00:17:02.319 --> 00:17:04.500
while on day patrol.

00:17:04.500 --> 00:17:10.350
He was upfront about his criminal past as
a bank robber but told her he had changed.

00:17:10.350 --> 00:17:14.250
He said he was a college graduate and
had a good paying job.

00:17:14.250 --> 00:17:15.590
He lied.

00:17:15.590 --> 00:17:20.380
His mother knew he was leading Kristen Baxter
on, and she threatened to not only tell Kristin

00:17:20.380 --> 00:17:24.839
but also to withdraw her own financial support
of Brett.

00:17:24.839 --> 00:17:29.850
With the wedding only weeks away, Brett decided
to take extreme actions to avoid the truth

00:17:29.850 --> 00:17:31.300
coming out.

00:17:31.300 --> 00:17:36.750
With only three weeks until his wedding, Brett
took matters into his own hands.

00:17:36.750 --> 00:17:41.581
Using the arrow from a crossbow he had stored
in his mother’s garage, he stabbed his mother

00:17:41.581 --> 00:17:45.680
in the chest and then proceeded to strangle
her in her garage.

00:17:45.680 --> 00:17:49.400
His younger brother Christopher heard the
struggle and came running.

00:17:49.400 --> 00:17:54.610
Aiming the cross bow at Christopher, Brett
show him in the neck with the arrow, and then

00:17:54.610 --> 00:17:58.930
hid his body under a tarp, along with their
mother’s body.

00:17:58.930 --> 00:18:03.950
Hearing the altercation, the eldest brother
Leigh came to investigate and was summarily

00:18:03.950 --> 00:18:09.580
attacked as well, but he managed to outrun
Brett and took refuge at a neighboring house

00:18:09.580 --> 00:18:12.060
where he was able to call the police.

00:18:12.060 --> 00:18:17.920
In the meantime, Brett’s older brother Alexander
then came over for unrelated reasons and was

00:18:17.920 --> 00:18:22.110
promptly stabbed in the driveway by one of
the crossbows arrows.

00:18:22.110 --> 00:18:25.530
He was found lying in the driveway when police
arrived.

00:18:25.530 --> 00:18:30.670
Brett tried to cover his tracks by creating
an electronic footprint at his house miles

00:18:30.670 --> 00:18:31.750
away.

00:18:31.750 --> 00:18:36.840
He attached a wooden cooking spoon onto a
string tied to the ceiling fan which would

00:18:36.840 --> 00:18:41.900
spin so that the spoon tapped the enter button
on the keyboard of his laptop, prompting the

00:18:41.900 --> 00:18:44.780
playing of various YouTube videos.

00:18:44.780 --> 00:18:49.860
He also pre-programmed his email to send various
messages from his home computer to make it

00:18:49.860 --> 00:18:54.750
appear as if he were home, and not killing
his entire family at their house.

00:18:54.750 --> 00:18:59.340
The technological alibi didn’t work and
Brett was arrested outside of his mothers

00:18:59.340 --> 00:19:00.340
home.

00:19:00.340 --> 00:19:04.510
He was charged with first-degree murder for
killing his brother Christopher, and two counts

00:19:04.510 --> 00:19:09.800
of second-degree murder for killing his mother
and their younger brother Alexander; he was

00:19:09.800 --> 00:19:13.410
also convicted of attempted murder of his
older brother Leigh.

00:19:13.410 --> 00:19:19.530
He received three concurrent life sentences,
with mandatory minimum sentence of 25 years

00:19:19.530 --> 00:19:21.660
until
He can apply for parole.

00:19:21.660 --> 00:19:25.890
Needless to say he never got married.

00:19:25.890 --> 00:19:26.890
5.

00:19:26.890 --> 00:19:29.790
Impress or Perish

00:19:29.790 --> 00:19:35.550
In a low level position at a children's psychiatric
unit of a Salt Lake City hospital, Mark Hacking

00:19:35.550 --> 00:19:39.240
always secretly idolized the doctors he worked
under.

00:19:39.240 --> 00:19:43.720
He wanted to be just like them, and through
a carefully constructed set of lies he was

00:19:43.720 --> 00:19:48.780
able to get everyone around him to believe
he was on the path to medical school.

00:19:48.780 --> 00:19:53.860
His family, including his wife Lori, believed
he had graduated with a bachelors degree from

00:19:53.860 --> 00:19:58.320
the University of Utah, but in actuality he
had dropped out.

00:19:58.320 --> 00:20:04.830
There had been hints of Marks lies for years,
though the Hackings never connected the dots.

00:20:04.830 --> 00:20:10.200
Three years prior to her death, Lori received
a voicemail from Marks mother, confused, stating

00:20:10.200 --> 00:20:14.180
how she had just attempted to pay Mark’s
undergraduate tuition but when she called

00:20:14.180 --> 00:20:17.880
the college they said he was not registered
as a student.

00:20:17.880 --> 00:20:22.720
Mark brushed it off saying he had just forgotten
to cross a few tees and for a few “i’s”

00:20:22.720 --> 00:20:26.670
in the registration process and that it was
all fixed now.

00:20:26.670 --> 00:20:31.270
His family believed he has worked it all out
and was a full time student who eventually

00:20:31.270 --> 00:20:35.780
graduated with honors, going to the fact that
his mother had helped him with his term papers

00:20:35.780 --> 00:20:39.670
and allowed him to keep his old textbooks
at her house.

00:20:39.670 --> 00:20:44.370
One year later he began an elaborate process
to make it look like he was applying to medical

00:20:44.370 --> 00:20:48.330
school after he seemingly received his undergraduate
degree.

00:20:48.330 --> 00:20:52.800
He would speak of the application process
and interviews extensively, even going so

00:20:52.800 --> 00:20:57.690
far as having his family members drive him
to prestigious Ivy League schools for so-called

00:20:57.690 --> 00:20:59.530
interviews.

00:20:59.530 --> 00:21:03.390
He flew to Manhattan where he stayed with
his cousin under the pretense of having an

00:21:03.390 --> 00:21:06.970
interview at the University of Columbia medical
school.

00:21:06.970 --> 00:21:11.540
Afterwards talking at length about how he
felt the interview went.

00:21:11.540 --> 00:21:15.710
Eventually Mark Told everyone he had been
accepted to the University of North Carolina

00:21:15.710 --> 00:21:21.090
medical school, and he and his wife Laurie
procured housing in North Carolina and prepared

00:21:21.090 --> 00:21:24.170
to embark on the cross-country move.

00:21:24.170 --> 00:21:28.610
Lori had quit her job at Wells Fargo and had
packed all their possessions in preparation

00:21:28.610 --> 00:21:31.280
for the upcoming relocation.

00:21:31.280 --> 00:21:35.080
During this time Lori found out that she was
pregnant.

00:21:35.080 --> 00:21:41.470
On the 15th of July 2004, Lori emailed Her
and Marks family their new address in Chapel

00:21:41.470 --> 00:21:47.720
Hill, NC, (whether the house was actually
there is or was another part of Mark’s lie

00:21:47.720 --> 00:21:51.090
is unknown as they would never move in).

00:21:51.090 --> 00:21:56.470
On 16 July Lori received a phone call from
the University of North Carolina which caused

00:21:56.470 --> 00:22:04.270
her to leave work early, crying and obviously
distraught.

00:22:04.270 --> 00:22:10.700
In the early hours of July 19th Mark called
police to report his wife as missing; he said

00:22:10.700 --> 00:22:14.280
she had left for an early morning jog and
never returned.

00:22:14.280 --> 00:22:20.120
The case garnered almost instant media tension
and Mark could be seen on live television

00:22:20.120 --> 00:22:25.080
making a plea for any information on his wife’s
whereabouts and thanking the search and rescue

00:22:25.080 --> 00:22:27.890
workers for doing their jobs.

00:22:27.890 --> 00:22:32.650
But in the days succeeding, Police quickly
became suspicious when his financial history

00:22:32.650 --> 00:22:39.040
revealed he bought a new bedroom mattress
in the minutes prior to making the 911 call.

00:22:39.040 --> 00:22:45.210
On July 20th Mark was reported by a nearby
hotel for walking in public naked with only

00:22:45.210 --> 00:22:46.880
his shoes on.

00:22:46.880 --> 00:22:51.250
He was checked into a psychiatric hospital
by his family, although many people thought

00:22:51.250 --> 00:22:56.490
him to be faking as experts pointed out that
had he truly gone crazy he would not have

00:22:56.490 --> 00:22:58.020
kept his shoes on.

00:22:58.020 --> 00:23:02.830
As the investigation continued to turn up
startling fax his family was notified that

00:23:02.830 --> 00:23:04.950
his life has been a lie.

00:23:04.950 --> 00:23:10.090
This led Mark‘s father to confronting him
and Mark admitted to brutally killing Lori

00:23:10.090 --> 00:23:13.940
while she slept and puttin her body in a dumpster.

00:23:13.940 --> 00:23:19.140
Police would find her badly decomposed body
buried under almost 2,000 pounds of garbage

00:23:19.140 --> 00:23:22.190
on October 1st in a landfill.

00:23:22.190 --> 00:23:25.650
Lori’s parents have memories of their daughter
all over the house.

00:23:25.650 --> 00:23:31.110
Thy have done their best to preserve all the
years of Lori’s life, up until her death.

00:23:31.110 --> 00:23:35.970
In the days following the news that Mark had
killed her, a digital photography company,

00:23:35.970 --> 00:23:42.000
Orem, offered to digitally erase Marc from
all of the family photos for free and Lori’s

00:23:42.000 --> 00:23:45.140
headstone has no mention of the Hacking name.

00:23:45.140 --> 00:23:50.870
Mark received 6 years to life, A sentence
that sound shocking and inspired a new law,

00:23:50.870 --> 00:23:55.880
Called Lori’s Law to make the mandatory
minimum for murder 15 years.

00:23:55.880 --> 00:24:02.800
Mark will be eligible for parole in 2035,
A sentence many believe is far too short.

00:24:02.800 --> 00:24:08.090
The worst part of it all says lawyers brother
is that none of this was necessary.

00:24:08.090 --> 00:24:12.420
He believes that Lori would’ve loved him
no matter what as long as he was trying his

00:24:12.420 --> 00:24:18.650
best, and that this elaborate lie Mark lead
was for him and not for her.

00:24:18.650 --> 00:24:23.620
The University of Utah has a Lori Hacking
scholarship in which every year two years

00:24:23.620 --> 00:24:29.630
of tuition are given to women who have overcome
adversity and startling circumstances to get

00:24:29.630 --> 00:24:30.740
where they are today.

